threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered hacktool. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, Intel 80386, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, for GNU/Linux 2.6.24, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a statically linked ELF executable. Its large size and the presence of numerous strings related to standard library functionality (e.g., `../sysdeps/unix/sysv/linux/getcwd.c`, `../iconv/skeleton.c`, `/proc/self/maps`) indicate it is linked with the GNU C Library (glibc). The inclusion of a legitimate bug reporting URL (`bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/eglibc/+bugs`) further supports this. No malicious behaviors such as persistence, obfuscation, or suspicious network activity were observed.
